# macOS external-tool manifest — the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for the tools that
# `tooling/dev/setup-mac-tools.sh` installs/upgrades (run by `pnpm setup:local`
# and `pnpm setup:mac-tools`). One tool per line:
#
#   <method>|<spec>|<note>
#
#   method  brew | npm | pipx | node | docker
#   spec    brew: formula · npm: package@version · pipx: package[extras]
#           node: (empty — the .nvmrc-pinned major is read automatically)
#           docker: the headless runtime formula to install if none is present
#   note    free text (shown in docs / for humans)
#
# Remove a line here → that tool is dropped from setup. Add a line → it's included.
# Order matters (top-to-bottom). Homebrew itself is bootstrapped by the script
# before this list (it's the install mechanism, not a listed tool). All installs
# come from authenticated sources only; blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.

node||Node.js — pinned .nvmrc major; existing nvm/fnm Node left alone; pnpm via corepack
brew|gitleaks|secret scan (pre-commit + CI)
brew|gh|GitHub CLI (env/ruleset sync, PR tooling)
brew|jq|JSON in shell/CI scripts
brew|uv|runtime for the uvx MCP servers
brew|pipx|isolated host for the headroom Python CLI
docker|colima|headless Docker runtime — only if none present (OrbStack/Docker Desktop respected)
npm|@colbymchenry/codegraph@latest|codegraph code-intelligence MCP
pipx|headroom-ai[mcp]|headroom context-compression MCP
